<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><listPerson xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0"><person xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xml:id="ALD04" sex="1"><persName xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0"><roleName xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">Dr</roleName><forename xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">James</forename><surname xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">Alderson</surname><addName xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0"/></persName><birth xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" when="1000"><placeName xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0"/></birth><death xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" when="1825-10-20"/><occupation xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">physician</occupation><note xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" type="editorial"><p xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">Dr James Alderson was the son of a dissenting minister (also James).  He grew up in East Anglia and settled in Norwich.  He had reformist sympathies. He was the father of 
  Godwin's intimate, <persName xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" key="ALD02">Amelia Opie née Alderson</persName>.</p><p xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">    'Alderson' entries have been coded as James (rather than Amelia, his
    daughter). The first recorded meeting is on Godwin's trip to Norwich in 1794 - when Dr Alderson
    calls upon him, after which there are several meetings (with the 'Dr.' being dropped after the
    first meeting). It is assumed by most biographers that Godwin meets Alderson for the first time
    at this point - but it may be that they knew each other in some respect from much earlier in
    Godwin's life, both being associated with dissenting circles in Norfolk. Suggestively, there is
    no mention of Alderson, father or daughter, in the lists of first meetings in the diary for
    1796. After the Norwich trip their next meeting is when Alderson calls with Godwin on the actress <persName xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" key="SID01">Sarah Siddons</persName> in
    London. (12 April 1795) There are several isolated London calls, then a period in July 1796 when
   Godwin visits Norwich again. 'Dr.' Alderson appears again in 1798 on one occasion, and then at
    Opies in 1799. There is then a further visit to Norwich in September/October1803 and a brief
    visit in 1805. </p><p xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">Godwin recorded his death.</p></note><bibl xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" type="other"><title xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">DNB</title>, entry for Amelia Opie, née Alderson</bibl><ab xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" type="appearancesInDiary"><ab xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" n="1788"/><ab xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" n="1789"/><ab xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" n="1790"/><ab xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" n="1791"/><ab xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" n="1792"/><ab xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" n="1793"/><ab xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" n="1794"><date xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" when="1794-06-26" n="notVenue" type="ah"/><date xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" when="1794-06-27" n="notVenue" type="ah"/><date xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" when="1794-06-28" n="venue" type="ah"/><date xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" when="1794-07-01" n="venue" type="ah"/><date xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" when="1794-07-05" n="venue" type="ah"/><date xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" when="1794-07-06" n="venue" type="ah"/></ab><ab xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" n="1795"><date xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" when="1795-04-12" n="notVenue" type="ah"/><date xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" when="1795-05-10" n="venue" type="ah"/><date xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" when="1795-06-16" n="venue" type="nah"/></ab><ab xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" n="1796"><date xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" when="1796-07-05" n="notVenue" type="ah"/><date xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" when="1796-07-08" n="notVenue" type="ah"/><date xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" when="1796-07-09" n="notVenue" type="ah"/><date xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" when="1796-07-10" n="notVenue" type="ah"/><date xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" when="1796-07-10" n="notVenue" type="ah"/><date xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" when="1796-07-10" n="not